# Branch Names

When creating or renaming a branch, follow the "Branch names" table in [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) (SSOT). Validate with `just brlint <name>` before creating the branch (or immediately after a rename).

- Prefer `feature/<slug>`, `bugfix/<slug>`, or `hotfix/<slug>` — the prefix drives merge routing.
- Put the issue number at the start of the slug when there is one (e.g. `feature/42-doctor-command`).
- Use `support/<slug>` or `release/<slug>` only when the human explicitly asks — the lint accepts them, but they have no special merge routing.
- Development is trunk-based: branch off `main` and merge back to `main` (see [branch-issue-resolution.md](../docs/branch-issue-resolution.md)).
